Text.Value: Fortunately, the Temple was destroyed, and to cleanse the city of Sarevok's memory, the Iron Throne was torn from its foundations and cast into the Chionthar.
What about the other victims on the list, the ones who are still alive?
But you've been investigating too, if I'm not mistaken? You're trying to stop your own kind?
I'm trying to hide from my Father's wrath. I fear what will happen if I delve too deeply.
Bhaal is trying to force me to be his Chosen. I'm doing all I can to resist him.
Anything else?
Now your turn. What do you know about this?
Leave.
I am working against Bhaal - I got a hold of the list of murder targets.
You're absolutely right. I have reasons of my own to think there's been an increase in Bhaalist activity.
Report back to me if you find anything. And thank you. If I'm right, you'll be doing a great service to the city.
You said Sarevok led the cultists a century ago - he can't still be alive, can he?
You're very excited about Bhaal for someone who's supposed to be protecting the city.

EditorData.logicalname: LOGIC: KNOWS BHAAL PLOT FROM TARGET LIST

Text.Value: I suppose it was quite an ask... but perhaps you wouldn't mind doing me a different, smaller favour?
You're a terrible liar. You've got something. Give it here.
Ah, hells. I will live to warn the Gate. FISTS!
What - FISTS! TO ME!
I am no stranger to hunting down vicious killers - be they man or beast. Perhaps I could help?
Tell her about the murder target list you found while investigating Lorgan's murder.
*She's not just reticent to share her theory - she's hiding a physical object. A document of some sort.*
Because I am going to kill you now - in his unholy name.
I've not ruled out the possibility that it is Sarevok himself.
For most, that was the end of it. But cults like that don't disappear overnight. This list you brought me confirms I'm right.
It's nice of you to indulge me, but I'm afraid this matter is a little too sensitive to share as a mere indulgence.
Are you Devella? Valeria sent me.
While I'm there, the other potential victims will be at risk. Could you warn them?
Corpses without hands are showing up all over the city. Together with dioramas of death and murder. It has to be connected.
I've been working on an assignment - a side-project of sorts. I think the removal of the hand is the key, but I just can't figure out how.
Take the uniform off, then. Go undercover.
Terrifying?
I'm going to stop my Father, whatever it takes.
Good. Then your eyes are open to the truth.
I'll leave you to your work.
Show her the list of murder targets.
You've had a busy tenday. I can't even imagine. Well, I'll tell you what I know.
The higher-ups don't want to hear that, of course. The last thing they need is public hysteria about a cult that was supposed to have died out over a century ago.
You should raise this with your superiors, immediately.

EditorData.logicalname: DOESNT KNOW DEVELLA TRIED TO ESCALATE

Text.Value: Very nice. Correct on most counts - you might prove useful.
I know more about Bhaal than anyone you'll find. You don't want to send me away.
You don't seem to understand - my job is to help the rich first.
Do you need some help? I've dealt with much worse than this.
Most of what I know is based on reading into Sarevok's history. I'm sure it's nothing next to your personal experience, but I'll share what I have.
Bhaal? That's exactly what I - wait. How do you know about that?

EditorData.NodeContext: with the realisation that her improbable conclusion/investigation was bang on the money but also still suspicious of the player (how do THEY know?!)

Text.Value: I'll do my best.
And the removal of the hand... I've a theory, but - well, you're a civilian. That one will be for me to follow up.
That's your job. Not my problem if you only want to help the rich.
Look, kid. I can see you mean well. But I'm not letting a civilian get involved.
Be quick about it too.
The symbol's the bit that bothers most. You use poison when you want to get away with murder. So why leave a symbol at the scene of the crime? It doesn't make any sense.
*Begrudgingly, you tell her about the murder target list you found.*
There, Sarevok amassed an army and sought to become a god. Under his stewardship, the Bhaal Temple was revived, and with it, the Bhaal cult itself.
For most, that was the end of it. But cults like that don't disappear overnight. That list you spoke of confirms I'm right.
I need to look into the Bhaalists, and fast. I think they're after me.
I'll see what I can find.
Here's all I've found. The duke was paralysed by poison, Absolutist symbol scrawled on the floor in blood. Hand removed pre-mortem.
Suppose it couldn't hurt - we're scraping the barrel as is right now.
Have you found something?
What makes you think it's not Sarevok himself?
Erm. [GEN_PlayerName_c11eee1e-7815-6143-7233-f2427799fa53], amnesiac, I care about preventing murders?
The ritualistic brutality of them... it's extraordinary. And it could only be the work of a Bhaalist.
Oh believe me, I wish I could. But that's above my paygrade. Besides, someone's got to oversee the investigation here.
Uh, [GEN_PlayerName_c11eee1e-7815-6143-7233-f2427799fa53], recently unemployed, I quite like murders?
Tell her of the target list. Say nothing of your intentions.
Are you sure I can't help?
Gods - that's it! Proof that I was right.
Sure as the stench of an ogre's latrine. Get lost.
Let me help you - I trained under Camber Fosrick, the world's greatest investigative mind.
I've been working on an assignment, see - a research project of sorts. I knew my conclusions were sound, but this... I never expected this.
No doubt you found a trail of bodies in their wake?
Once I've secured the patriars, I'll head to Basilisk Gate. Meet me there if you have a change of heart.
The people of the Gate are fortunate another of Bhaal's children stands against him. Walk in light.
If what you claim is true, you wouldn't be helping me here unless you were trying to end Bhaal's hold over you.
It's becoming something of an obsession of mine. You see, these murders have been cropping up all over the city.
I tried to explain all this to my superiors, but they wouldn't have any of it.
I found another murder victim. Absolute symbol nearby, just like Stelmane.
Not from around here, are you? We're in Baldur's Gate - this is just how things work.
Then I hope you can at least protect yourself, and pray this plot fails.
I'll bet if you follow the trail of these murders, you'll be able to unearth the truth of this resurgence.
Oh, you saw? I suppose there's no harm in sharing it with you. It's just a theory, after all...
Tell her about the murder target list you found.
But that doesn't get us any closer to motive.
YOU. Name, rank, and reason for interrupting an active crime scene. For your sake, the last one better be bloody good.
*She's tense, that much is clear to see. But her professional veneer is simply too resistant to amateur probing.*
The Bhaal cult is back, and someone is out there, continuing Sarevok's work.
There are patriars on the murder target list. I'm oathbound to secure them first, so I'll be heading to the Upper City next.
Hmm. That tracks. The killer paralyses the victim with poison. And wine is a perfectly innocuous vessel for it.
Well? Have you found anything?
Get back to it, then. Lives depend on it. Literally.
There's more at stake than Stelmane's murder now that Bhaal himself is involved.
I'd follow up myself, but while this uniform gets me into certain places, it keeps me out of others. Especially places that don't want to be found...
They told me to drop it. Told me the city doesn't need another conspiracy theorist and to get back to doing my job before they find someone else to do it for me.
You're lucky you met me - most of the Fist wouldn't have believed you were a Bhaalspawn. Think it's Baldurian superstition.
Can't you help me?
The precision of the cuts, the depth, the execution - the best butchers in Faern couldn't make a cut like that. Trust me, I've asked them.
Abhorrent?
Any idea who it is?
I know a lot about Bhaal. I suspect he's involved with this.
What? I've got a duke's murder to solve, and not a lot of time to do it.
Ah, another sceptic. You should consider joining the Fist. You'll find plenty of like-minded folks.
But before you run and hide, there are a few more lives you could easily save.
Don't get your hopes up, but do report back if you find something. The people of Baldur's Gate will be grateful for a breakthrough in this case.
Show her the target list. Say nothing of your intentions.
A century ago, Bhaal bred dozens just like you. One of whom was Sarevok Anchev.
Perfect. Unofficially, mind. As far as the higher-ups are concerned, you're still just a civilian. If you end up breaking any laws, well - I won't be able to help you.
I can't help you. I've got business of my own.
You're doing a grand job. I hope the person who solves your murder will be just as diligent.

EditorData.NodeContext: she realises the player is threatening to kill her

Text.Value: It's my job to be. Though I confess it has been very interesting.
It's simple really. I kill you, as an offering to Bhaal.

EditorData.logicalname: KILLED FIRST TARGET + NOT UNHOLY ASSASSIN

Text.Value: Use the crime scene to describe how Stelmane was killed. Show her you can help solve this.
You're not wrong about the cult. I found some Bhaalists in the sewers.
I'll see what else I can find here, but keep your eye out in the city. There'll be more corpses soon, if we can't figure this out.
Stranger things have come back to haunt this city.
No idea, unfortunately. But whoever it is, they are intimately familiar with Sarevok's work.
You see, these murders have been cropping up all over the city. I've been following their trail for a while now, and tracing it back to its roots.
Tell me your theory. Perhaps I can help.
You're a terrible liar. Tell me everything - now.
A hobbyist detective? I can't fault the drive - I read the Baldur's Mouth crime reports like a starving wereboar before I worked for the Fist.
I've got better things to do than investigate a cult.
I understand. I'll look into this Bhaalist resurgence for you.
But you - you're not bound by such constraints. Help me out, here. Help the city out.
Unlikely?
I found this bottle of wine - it's poisonous.
Once I'm done with the patriars, I'll head to Basilisk Gate to have another go at convincing my superiors to put some resources into this matter.
Isn't it enough that I already agreed to investigate the murder trail?
Oh bollocks - I told those idiots not to let anyone through.
Not yet.
A century ago, there was a man - Sarevok Anchev. He was a child of the god of murder, Bhaal.
It's fascinating!
Remind me what I'm looking for?
I'm lost. I'll leave you alone.
I can't help you.
Yes, I'm Devella, the unfortunate colleague.
Tell her about the target list.
Now if you don't mind, I've work to do.
Gods save us all if you're right, but I'd believe it. Whoever it is, they are intimately familiar with Sarevok's work.
Good luck, then.
Another? Whoever's behind this is certainly effective, and I've no more Fists to spare. Tell me you've found something else that could actually help us?
Believe me, I wish I could. But I need this job.
I am here to sacrifice you, I'm afraid.
Everyone does in this city. All right, but keep your eyes peeled, and your mouth shut. If you find anything, tell me, but best not to go alarming the other Fists.
Leave.
Why are you so angry?
You're better off not raising any suspicions. Trust me.
I've seen my share of dead bodies. Maybe I can be of help?
Unfortunate?
I think it may be another Bhaalspawn...
Something, anything that can link these murders to the Bhaalist resurgence.
The Flaming Fist should be protecting everyone - not just Upper City folk.
Not only is the cult back, it's spreading fast. I ran into some Bhaalists in the park.
Half the silkroot-chewers in the Gate have claimed to be a Bhaalspawn at one point. The Fist don't listen to ghost stories.
Uh, [GEN_PlayerName_c11eee1e-7815-6143-7233-f2427799fa53], adventurer, curiosity?
If anyone can, it will be you. Or at least that's what the legends say.
The key to solving a murder is to understand the motive. The ritualistic nature of these killings point to the Absolute, but I don't buy it. It's too convenient.
The brutality of the killings is certainly reminiscent of his work. But there's something more here, something new...
Recount your investigation into Father Lorgan's murder, and show her the list you found.
What's that you're hiding?
Try to read her body language.
I know a lot about Bhaal. I suspect he's involved with this.
What will you do in the meantime?
Leave.
I'll tell you what I know.
Trust me on this: it was an aspiring Bhaal cultist.
Was it an aspiring Bhaal cultist by any chance?
I'll see what I can do.
Follow the trail of these murders. Prove the truth. Use your lineage to get places the Fist can't.
Look, I'd love to stand around and chat, but there's work to be done.
The brutality of it, the unnecessary brutality... My theory is that it's got something to do with the Lord of Murder himself - Bhaal.
There's a reverence to these murders, a certain flair. It's as if they were done in worship.
You really are a godsend. But - one more thing...
Oh! Oh my. By Ilmater's rack, that's... that's...
Never mind me - how do you know about Bhaal's resurgence?
They're always the same - victim paralysed by poison, Absolutist symbol scrawled on the floor in blood. Hand removed pre-mortem.
Nice try. That name's straight out of those dreadful Cormyr detective stories. Get lost - I've work to do.
An adventurer. Fantastic. We don't have enough of those in Baldur's Gate.
Hells, you might be the only one who can stop this. What else do you know?
I was just fearmongering for fun. Bhaal's not back. Everything is fine.
I'm no one - just another adventurer.
I think it may be a Bhaalspawn...
Meet me there if you've anything more to report. And good luck.
Tell her about the murder target list you found.
To fetch her another bottle of mead, no doubt.
You seemed capable - it would have been remiss of me not to ask. But I understand.
You're going to want to see this. Show her the murder target list.
Gods... This is it. The proof that I was right!

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Devella takes and studies the list

Text.Value: I have seen death and cruelty in all its forms. Perhaps I could be of service?
I don't know much. I only just found out I was a Bhaalspawn in a vision.
Don't you think I've tried? They won't listen.
Nor does it tie this back to the Bhaalist resurgence.
He ruled the Iron Throne - a dark tower hiding a darker secret. It was the front for a deadly arms-dealing network.
Of course. You're a civilian. You shouldn't be involved in this.
I was hoping you could tell me more.
I've done everything I can within the remit of my job. Any more, and they'll fire me.
I know a lot about Bhaal. I suspect he's involved with this.
Useful information like this? Show her the murder target list.
And the removal of the hand pre-mortem... the unnecessary brutality of it - it's got to be connected to Bhaal, it's just got to be.
I'm working against Bhaal - I found the murderer's target list.
But before you run off, do you think you could save a few more lives?
You are here to help me, and not to sacrifice me, aren't you?
Don't panic, but I'm sort of... his son.
Don't panic, but I'm sort of... his daughter.
Don't panic, but I'm sort of... his spawn.
Valeria said you might want to see this. Show her the murder target list.
If you find something, let me know. But don't get your hopes up. I certainly won't.
Recount your investigation into Father Lorgan's murder, and what you remember of the list you found.

EditorData.logicalname: Alias (LOGIC: KNOWS BHAAL PLOT FROM TARGET LIST)

Text.Value: Thank you for your interest, citizen, but I'd best get back to doing the real work. Alone.
But you should leave it to the professionals. It's not healthy for civilians to see scenes of such a sensitive nature.
Just like the wayward Bhaalspawn who saved the Gate before...
I'm chasing down a serial killer who seems to kill without motive. You try doing that and staying calm.
So it's all happening again... just like in Sarevok's time...
Lucky you! The future Chosen of Bhaal stands before you, and you will be his offering!
Lucky you! The future Chosen of Bhaal stands before you, and you will be her offering!
Lucky you! The future Chosen of Bhaal stands before you, and you will be their offering!
But fine, if you're not interested in helping, I guess I'll just have to try and convince my superiors to put some resources into this matter.
Goodbye.
I know a lot about Bhaal. I suspect he's involved with this.
Father has shown me visions - the Temple of Bhaal lurks somewhere in the city.
I should arrest you at once, but - well, the Bhaalspawn crisis, it's the most interesting criminal plight in Baldurian history.
Thank you. That's all I can ask, and more than I hoped.
I'm glad you're on the right side of this, Bhaalspawn. You could be invaluable, if you can get on the inside.
I'm planning to infiltrate the cult, but I don't know where to start.
I thought I made myself very clear, civilian. Move along.
Unless you've got useful information, leave me to my work. Duke Stelmane's dead - and I've got to find who killed her.
The brutality of the killings is on a par with Sarevok's own. But there's something more here, something new...

Synopsis: Dialog with Devella Fountainhead at Elfsong Tavern. This dialog only can be played once. After dialog, Devella will go away.
